sources.title: Articles on Smashing Magazine — For Web Designers And Developers

articles.author: hello@smashingmagazine.com (Cosima Mielke & Geoff Graham)
articles.description: How can we create products and experiences that don’t cause harm to the planet and to the people who use them? What do we need to consider to make more sustainable design decisions and reduce the carbon footprint of our websites? In this post, we compiled valuable resources that will get you familiar with the principles of sustainable design.
articles.title: Sustainable Design Toolkits And Resources

articles.author: hello@smashingmagazine.com (Cosima Mielke)
articles.description: Let’s welcome the new month with some fresh desktop wallpapers. Designed by artists and designers from around the globe, they come in versions with and without a calendar for July 2023. Enjoy!
articles.title: Off To New Adventures (July 2023 Wallpapers Edition)

articles.author: hello@smashingmagazine.com (Vitaly Friedman)
articles.description: The design process is messy. You might be following a structured approach, but too often, it takes a life of its own. And before you know it, you are designing in chaos, with last-minute changes and missed deadlines. So, what’s the “perfect” design process?
articles.title: What’s The Perfect Design Process?

articles.author: hello@smashingmagazine.com (Patrick Brosset)
articles.description: Let’s discover the most popular DevTools tips that can boost your productivity and revolutionize your debugging workflow.
articles.title: Useful DevTools Tips and Tricks

articles.author: hello@smashingmagazine.com (Geoff Graham)
articles.description: The Wikipedia team shipped a redesign of the ubiquitous and one of the [most visited websites](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_most_visited_websites) on the web. Alex Hollender and Jon Robson led the work and generously discussed the effort with us in a thorough, wide-ranging interview that covers the design, development, and processes that went into the project.
articles.title: Behind The Curtains Of Wikipedia Redesign

articles.author: hello@smashingmagazine.com (Mikołaj Dobrucki)
articles.description: In today’s article, let’s explore how we can use Flex Layout and see how it empowers designers with greater control over their work while saving everyone’s time.
articles.title: Penpot’s Flex Layout: Building CSS Layouts In A Design Tool

articles.author: hello@smashingmagazine.com (Joas Pambou)
articles.description: Dive into an article where you will build an app that evaluates audio files for positive and negative sentiments. The idea is that you will create an interface for uploading an audio file, then transcribe the contents into text before analyzing the text and assigning it a positive or negative score for how the tone is perceived.
articles.title: Using AI To Detect Sentiment In Audio Files

articles.author: hello@smashingmagazine.com (Scott Gallant)
articles.description: Visual editing is beginning to make its way into headless architecture and the early results look promising. We’ll look at a few headless CMSs that currently support visual editing in this article.
articles.title: Visual Editing Comes To The Headless CMS

articles.author: hello@smashingmagazine.com (Juan Diego Rodríguez)
articles.description: Part 2 of the series concentrates on implementing internationalization (i18n) on a Gatsby website, an essential feature on any multilingual website that can be quite a bit of trouble if incorrectly implemented, creating more problems than it solves.
articles.title: Gatsby Headaches And How To Cure Them: i18n (Part 2)

articles.author: hello@smashingmagazine.com (Ren Chen)
articles.description: One way of getting a more behind-the-scenes experience of any Smashing event is to apply as a volunteer, and Ren did just that! The SmashingConf team organized a conference in good ol’ San Francisco this year, and here’s pretty much how it went down.
articles.title: What Was SmashingConf In San Franciso Like?

articles.author: hello@smashingmagazine.com (Geoff Graham)
articles.description: [Codux](https://codux.hopp.to/smashing) is a new visual IDE brought to you by the fine folks over at[ Wix](https://www.wix.com/). It’s got a lot of low-code features that level the playing field for app development but is really designed for React developers. How so, you ask? That’s what we’re going to explore in this article.
articles.title: Meet Codux: The React Visual Editor That Improves Developer Experience

articles.author: hello@smashingmagazine.com (Sriram Thiagarajan)
articles.description: SvelteKit is a framework for building apps using Svelte. In this article, Sriram shows you how to build a server-side rendered (SSR) SvelteKit application and deploy it to Netlify by following this step-by-step guide.
articles.title: How To Build Server-Side Rendered (SSR) Svelte Apps With SvelteKit

articles.author: hello@smashingmagazine.com (Drew McLellan)
articles.description: In this episode of The Smashing Podcast, we ask what is a design manager? What does it take and how does it relate to the role of Designer? Vitaly talks to Slava Shestopalov to find out.
articles.title: Smashing Podcast Episode 62 With Slava Shestopalov: What Is Design Management?

articles.author: hello@smashingmagazine.com (Juan Diego Rodríguez)
articles.description: In this first part of a two-part hands-on guide, Juan Rodriguez explains how to use several i18n plugins for Gatsby and reviews some others.
articles.title: Gatsby Headaches And How To Cure Them: i18n (Part 1)

articles.author: hello@smashingmagazine.com (Paul Boag)
articles.description: Unleash the power of creative limitation! Learn how constraints aren’t barriers but instead stepping stones to innovative design. Find out how to challenge unproductive restrictions and leverage the rest to your advantage.
articles.title: Design Under Constraints: Challenges, Opportunities, And Practical Strategies

articles.author: hello@smashingmagazine.com (Slava Shestopalov & Eugene Shykiriavyi)
articles.description: While compliance with accessibility checklists is essential, it doesn’t necessarily mean a pleasant experience. That’s why live sessions can give you lots of priceless insights.
articles.title: Testing Sites And Apps With Blind Users: A Cheat Sheet

articles.author: hello@smashingmagazine.com (Yuliia Nikitina)
articles.description: This article covers the best tips and recommendations on the elements to pay attention to, the rules to follow, and life hacks to get around certain difficulties in table design.
articles.title: Exploring Universal And Cognitive-Friendly UX Design Through Pivot Tables And Grids

articles.author: Arunachalam B
articles.description: In today's highly competitive mobile app landscape, effectively engaging your app's users and delivering timely information is key.  Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM) is a powerful push notification service provided by Firebase. It offers a seamless way to connect with your app's users and keep them engaged.  In this
articles.title: How to Set Up Firebase Cloud Messaging in Flutter Using Firebase

articles.author: Rahul
articles.description: Ever feel like you’ve mastered the basics of Linux and are ready to level up your skills? Well, good news – there are many powerful commands that you might not know about. In this article, I'll introduce you to some lesser-known Linux commands that will help you become a more
articles.title: Helpful Linux Commands You Should Know

articles.author: Njoku Samson Ebere
articles.description: Authentication is a key security feature of any application. But it can be complex to implement properly. This tutorial will show you an easy and secure way to handle authentication in your apps. It involves allowing trusted organizations (such as Google, Facebook, Github, and so on) to authenticate your users
articles.title: How to Authenticate Users in Next.js With NextAuth – App Router VS Pages Router

articles.author: Beau Carnes
articles.description: Is this a hot dog? What about this image? We just published a course on the freeCodeCamp.org YouTube channel that will teach you all about Convolutional Neural Networks. Then you will build a project that can determine if an image is a hot dog or not a hot dog! Kylie
articles.title: Hot dog or not hot dog? Find out with Convolutional Neural Networks

articles.author: Omer Rosenbaum
articles.description: One of the most powerful tools a developer can have in their toolbox is git rebase. Yet it is notorious for being complex and misunderstood.  The truth is, if you understand what it actually does, git rebase is a very elegant, and straightforward tool to achieve so many different
articles.title: The Git Rebase Handbook – A Definitive Guide to Rebasing

articles.author: Clinton Joy
articles.description: You've probably come across carousels in many modern-day applications. Known by various names such as sliders or rotators, these versatile web elements showcase content in a visually appealing, sliding, or rotating manner.  Carousels can help you save space as well as enhance your User Interface and provide a great
articles.title: How to Build an Image Carousel with React and Framer Motion

articles.author: Md. Fahim Bin Amin
articles.description: If you want to learn MySQL, starting with a good client is super helpful – especially when you are just beginning your journey. There are a lot of clients out there for your MySQL-based needs, like XAMPP, DataGrip, and others. Among all of them, I prefer the MySQL Workbench [https://www.mysql.com/products/workbench/].
articles.title: How to Install MySQL and MySQL Workbench on Windows

articles.author: David Clinton
articles.description:
Using HTML tags like

articles.title: How to Work with CSS Style Sheets – the Basics for Beginners

articles.author: Valentine Gatwiri
articles.description: In the field of machine learning, there are two approaches: supervised learning and unsupervised learning. And it all depends on whether your data is labeled or not. Labels shape the way models are trained and affect how we gather insights from them. In this article, we'll explore the concepts of
articles.title: Supervised vs Unsupervised Learning – What's the Difference?

articles.author: Beau Carnes
articles.description: Embark on a journey through the realms of 3D game development with a new video course on the freeCodeCamp.org YouTube channel. Designed by the experienced game developer Omar Zaki, this course will help you master the creation of a 3D Action Role-Playing Game (RPG) with the open source Godot engine.
articles.title: Create a 3D RPG Game with Godot
